+# Framework Endpoint Freezing
+
+Reusable findings from the Step-008 setup gate that must freeze one coherent
+framework before any fresh host-space ranking.
+
+## Entries
+
+- `only-the-inherited-suitable-weak-leray-hopf-plus-lei-floor-has-a-locally-frozen-theorem-endpoint.md`:
+  the only locally supported framework is the inherited suitable-weak /
+  Leray-Hopf plus LEI floor, with the CKN/Lin epsilon-regularity contradiction
+  package as its live theorem endpoint.
+- `critical-space-language-does-not-become-a-framework-without-one-explicit-bridge-package.md`:
+  `L^3` and `\dot H^{1/2}` may remain serious critical-space languages, but
+  they do not become frozen frameworks without one explicit bridge or
+  replacement package and one chosen endpoint packet.
+- `without-one-frozen-temporal-package-the-branch-should-stop-before-host-space-audit.md`:
+  if framework, endpoint, and temporal packaging are not frozen together, the
+  branch should stop before reopening a Step-1 host-space audit.
